5.  FOR THE FIRST TIME THIS YEAR, THE NUMBER OF 
SHORT-TIME WORKERS WORKING LESS THAN 50 PERCENT OF THEIR 
REGULAR WORK SCHEDULES SHRANK FASTER THAN THE NUMBER OF 
SHORT-TIMERS WITH LONGER WORKING HOURS. 
 
